us shaded CGLIB/ASM internals and declares javax.inject/aopalliance dependencies, but meaningful AOP/proxy coverage on modern JDKs needs java.lang opened for old CGLIB reflective class definition.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"When tests exercise Guice method interception, CGLIB proxy creation, or other runtime bytecode generation, configure the test JVM and native-image build with `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` as the existing 2.1.7 test scaffold does. Prefer public Guice APIs (`com.google.inject.*`, `com.google.inject.matcher.Matchers`, `org.aopalliance.intercept.*`) and avoid importing the old unprefixed internal classes from the 2.1.7 tests; in 2.9.1 many shaded internal classes are present under `$`-prefixed names and are not stable user-facing APIs.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The reported javac failure is caused by tests importing internal classes whose names changed between 2.1.7 and 2.9.1, not by a missing external dependency.\",\n    \"Basic injector/binding coverage can run without extra setup, but AOP/proxy coverage fails on strongly encapsulated JDKs without the add-opens JVM/native-image argument.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_04545922b4af4731016a4210ac300c8193bc873f368dfd3d10\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1004, "output": 728, "cacheRead": 37888, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 39620, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782714532556, "responseId": "resp_04545922b4af4731016a4210a51e588193926ff8b377bf5eb5"}}
